SubItem.Name: SubIndex 000
SubItem.Comment: This object contains Parameters about the Connected Power supply Device.

SubItem.Name: Power supply EtherCAT Address
SubItem.Comment: Please enter the EtherCAT Address of the connected Power supply device here.

SubItem.Name: Address valid
SubItem.Comment: Shall be set to TRUE internally, if the given power supply EtherCAT Address is valid.

SubItem.Name: Readdata valid
SubItem.Comment: Shall be set to TRUE internally, if the given power supply read data is valid.

SubItem.Name: Device compatible
SubItem.Comment: Shall be set to TRUE internally, if the connected power supply is detected as compatible.

SubItem.Name: Actual DC link voltage
SubItem.Comment: Actual voltage value at the DC link.

SubItem.Name: Actual DC link out 1 current
SubItem.Comment: Actual current at DC output 1.

SubItem.Name: Actual DC link out 1 load utilization
Actual DC link out 1 overload utilization
DC link max voltage
SubItem.Comment: Threshold for dc link overvoltage error. The brake resistor switchOn threshold voltage 2C29:30 (calculated from this parameter) must be greater than mains overvoltage threshold xSqrt(2).

SubItem.Name: DC link continuous overcurrent warning threshold
SubItem.Comment: By actual motoric load (6001:04) above this value (percent of nominal dc link current) the DC link continuous overcurrent warning (6002:04) is set.

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor select mode
SubItem.Comment: According to this value following modes can be set: disable(0) or external (2).

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor power warning threshold
SubItem.Comment: Percent of brake resistor max power (8000:0c) and percent of brake resistor max short time energy (1 second on-time), above which the brake resistor power overload warning (6002:02) is set.

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor value
SubItem.Comment: Resistance value of brake resistor.

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor continuous power
SubItem.Comment: Brake resistor continuous power.

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor time constant 1
SubItem.Comment: Short time constant for thermal brake resistor model.

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor time constant 2
SubItem.Comment: Long time constant for thermal brake resistor model.

SubItem.Name: Brake resistor partial fraction factor
SubItem.Comment: Partial fraction factor for thermal brake resistor model in relation to short time constant.

SubItem.Name: Device temperature warning threshold
SubItem.Comment: Percent of heatsink max temperature, above which the device overtemperature warning (6002:03) is set.

SubItem.Name: Debug index
SubItem.Comment: Select internal values by id/symbol to be displayed or written at "Debug value.." (SubIdx 0x03).

SubItem.Name: Debug value float
SubItem.Comment: Actual value or value to be written at selected "Debug index" (SubIdx 0x01).

SubItem.Name: Debug value string
SubItem.Comment: Actual value or value to be written at selected "Debug index" (SubIdx 0x01).

SubItem.Name: Type debug pointer 1
SubItem.Comment: Lenght in bytes of internal variable to be debugged by debug pointer 1.

SubItem.Name: Address debug pointer 1
SubItem.Comment: 32-bit memory address of internal variable for debug pointer 1.

SubItem.Name: Type debug pointer 2
SubItem.Comment: Lenght in bytes of internal variable to be debugged by debug pointer 2.

SubItem.Name: Address debug pointer 2
SubItem.Comment: 32-bit memory address of internal variable for debug pointer 2.

SubItem.Name: Type debug pointer 3
SubItem.Comment: Lenght in bytes of internal variable to be debugged by debug pointer 3.

SubItem.Name: Address debug pointer 3
SubItem.Comment: 32-bit memory address of internal variable for debug pointer 3.

SubItem.Name: Type debug pointer 4
SubItem.Comment: Lenght in bytes of internal variable to be debugged by debug pointer 4.

SubItem.Name: Address debug pointer 4
SubItem.Comment: 32-bit memory address of internal variable for debug pointer 4.

SubItem.Name: Type debug pointer 5
SubItem.Comment: Lenght in bytes of internal variable to be debugged by debug pointer 5.

SubItem.Name: Address debug pointer 5
SubItem.Comment: 32-bit memory address of internal variable for debug pointer 5.

SubItem.Name: Type debug pointer 6
SubItem.Comment: Lenght in bytes of internal variable to be debugged by debug pointer 6.

SubItem.Name: Address debug pointer 6
SubItem.Comment: 32-bit memory address of internal variable for debug pointer 6.

SubItem.Name: DC link min voltage
SubItem.Comment: Minimal DC link voltage for device to be ready to operate.

SubItem.Name: Brake chopper switch on threshold voltage
SubItem.Comment: Voltage threshold, above which the brake chopper is switched on.

SubItem.Name: Brake chopper switch off threshold voltage
SubItem.Comment: Voltage threshold, below which the brake chopper is switched off.

SubItem.Name: DC link nominal current
SubItem.Comment: Nominal current supported by device at DC link.

SubItem.Name: DC link peak overcurrent threshold
SubItem.Comment: Current threshold to set the error "Peak over current (device output side)".

SubItem.Name: DC link max voltage
SubItem.Comment: Maximal DC link voltage threshold supported by device.

SubItem.Name: Device max temperature
SubItem.Comment: Maximal heatsink temperature supported by device, above which the error "Excess temperature device" is set.

SubItem.Name: Command
SubItem.Comment: Data type to be written in EEPROM

SubItem.Name: Command data string
SubItem.Comment: Value of Data type (8002:12) to be written in EEPROM

SubItem.Name: Command data integer
SubItem.Comment: By rising edge, slave in PREOP and right password the factory settings (2000) are written in the EEPROM. Internal use only.

A timeout has occurred.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: A parameterization error has occurred.
Brake chopper failured.

CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: Your connected brake resistor (internal or external) was overloaded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Current at connected brake resistor is too high. The brake resistor may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Check whether your brake resistor is damaged, if external one connected. Try to operate power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: No connected brake resistor can be detected.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake resistor is faulty and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is missing and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Plug in the connection bridge or connect an external brake resistor.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is not pugged in, an external brake resistor has been connected but this may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your external brake resistor. If this is not damaged, try to operate the power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

Failure at I2C bus.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An I2C-member is hanging and a reset of the I2C-bus failed.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch them on again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.
